==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
From the base of [[στρατία]]  {{GG|4756}} and [[ἄγω]] {{GG|71}} or [[ἡγέομαι]] {{GG|2233}}; 

===Pronunciation===
στρατηγός / stratēgos / strat-ay-gos'

===Noun===
'''στρατηγός'''

# a [[general]], that is, (by implication or analogy) a (military) governor (praetor), the chief (praefect) of the (Levitical) temple wardens: - [[captain]], [[magistrate]].

